evaluation.response:
It seems like you're feeling overwhelmed by the conflicting voices in your head. You'll know when it's the right time to take steps toward healing.&#x20;

Here are some factors to consider:&#x20;

*   Staying in control: However, this control may be causing more harm than good.
*   The cost of good health: Controlled eating, restrictive exercise, and lack of sleep can cause your health to spiral out of control.&#x20;
*   The benefits of healing: Once you do reach out for support, you can start the healing process and slowly start taking control of your body. You can address the fears that stop you from eating, create a plan with a trusted health professional, and learn new ways of taking care of yourself.

It's understandable to feel scared about what might happen if you stop the things that give you control. It's okay if this journey feels slow-going—after all, healing isn't an instant process. Odds are, you might need some direction and help from others in the process.&#x20;
